    </ul>

    <h2>3. The Service</h2>
    <p>
      Macroline lets you log foods, see daily calorie and macronutrient totals, set goals, and (with a Pro subscription) use AI features to log meals from natural-language descriptions, scan barcodes, and connect to compatible AI assistants via the Model Context Protocol (MCP).
    </p>
    <p>
      Macroline relies on public food databases (USDA FoodData Central, OpenFoodFacts), official restaurant nutrition pages, manufacturer-published data, and AI-derived estimates. Each food in our database carries a "source tier" indicating where the data came from. We make reasonable efforts to keep this data accurate but do not guarantee it.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Important disclaimer — not medical, dietary, or nutritional advice</h2>
    <p class="warn">
      <strong>Macroline is informational only.</strong> The calorie counts, macronutrient values, goal recommendations, and AI-generated outputs in the Service are not medical, dietary, nutritional, or fitness advice. Macroline is not a substitute for consultation with a licensed physician, registered dietitian, or other qualified professional.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Do not use Macroline to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease or health condition.</li>
      <li>Consult a qualified healthcare provider before making changes to your diet, exercise, or medication based on anything you see in the Service — particularly if you have a medical condition (including but not limited to diabetes, kidney disease, eating disorders, or pregnancy).</li>
      <li>Macros and calories shown for restaurant or branded items can change without notice. Verify with the source if accuracy is critical.</li>
      <li>If you are struggling with disordered eating, please consider reaching out to a qualified professional. In the US, the National Eating Disorders Association helpline is 1-800-931-2237.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Subscriptions, billing, and refunds</h2>

    <h3>Plans</h3>
    <p>
      Macroline offers a free tier with usage limits and a Pro subscription priced at <strong>$4.99 per month</strong> or <strong>$39.99 per year</strong>. Current pricing and feature lists are on our <a href="https://macroline.app/pricing">pricing page</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>Auto-renewal</h3>
    <p>
      Subscriptions auto-renew at the end of each billing period unless you cancel before that period ends. You will be charged for the next period using the payment method on file. We may attempt to retry payment if a charge fails.
    </p>

    <h3>Cancellation</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Subscriptions purchased on iOS:</strong> manage and cancel in your iPhone's <em>Settings → [Your Name] → Subscriptions → Macroline</em>. Per Apple's App Store policy, cancellations take effect at the end of the current billing period.</li>
      <li><strong>Subscriptions purchased on the web (via Stripe):</strong> manage via the Stripe customer portal link in your billing email. Cancellations take effect at the end of the current billing period.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Refunds</h3>
    <p>
      Subscription fees are non-refundable except where required by law. We do not provide partial refunds for unused time within a billing period. iOS refunds are handled by Apple per <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com">Apple's refund policy</a>. Web subscription refund requests can be sent to <a href="mailto:info@macroline.app">info@macroline.app</a> and will be considered case-by-case.
